result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Court calls  16CM115 & 16CM149 @ 11:45 am. Defendant Jamie Lynn Marten in court with attorney Gary Stephen Dodge.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State gives plea agreement DRI- 16CM115, 16CM149 Ct 2 DRI, ct's 1 & 3 plea, withheld sentence 18 months probation, concurrent, costs, DNA Surcharge, AODA and comply with treatment, Prescription take as prescribe. Def. admits prior convictions.  Def. advised of charges and penalties. Def. Ct 1 Attempt Retail Theft, repeater, no contest plea, Ct 3 Bailjumping, repeater, no contest plea. DRI ct 2. Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights.  Def. advised of constitutional rights & JT rights. Atty Dodge is satisfied.  Court accepts pleas and finds def. Guilty to Ct 1 Attempted retail theft, repeater, Ct 3 Bailjumping, repeater.  DRI Ct 2.  Def. has nothing to say.  Court orders
Ct 1 withheld sentence 18 months probation, costs, DNA surcharge and Sample, AODA and comply with treatment recommendations, Maintain Absolute Sobriety, 1 day credit if revoked. 
Ct 3 withheld sentence 18 months probation, concurrent to ct 1, costs, AODA & Absolute Sobriety. 
If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. No restitution.  State complied with victim rights. Def. advised of postconviction rights.  
16CM115 DRI, Bond to be applied to 16CM149.
Plea/sentencing hearing on February 28, 2017 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Jamie Lynn Marten in court with attorney Gary Stephen Dodge.  Jill Louise Laufenberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 15CM115, 16CM149, 16TR500 & 16TR501 @ 3:48 pm. State has spoke to City Atty Behrens, and State can handle TR cases.  Atty Dodge gives statement, misunderstanding between defendant and counsel.  City is requesting 845 fine, 7months revocation. State will honer.  16TR501, OWI, No contest & Finding Guilty and orders $845.00 fine and 7 months revocation and alcohol assessment and follow through. 16TR500 Dismissed. Def. given p.p.  All outstanding amount due will be added to one p.p. Criminal matter will be set for J.T. 16CM115 will be held 1st.  FPT Counsel and Def. need to appear.  Final pre-trial scheduled for November 28, 2016 at 03:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for December 14, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Status conference on September 12, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Jamie Lynn Marten in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls  16CM115, 16TR500 & 16TR501 @ 2:33 pm.  Atty Schuster enters Not Guilty plea. Court receives Not Guilty pleas.  Bond remains.  Traffic citations will continue to follow.  Status conference scheduled for August 8, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
